examples.en: The border extends to the river.
The plateau extends for many miles.
The forest extends beyond the border.
Her influence extends beyond the Beltway.
His power extends over the whole country.
The table extends to eight feet in length.
The shelf extends 20 cms from the bookcase.
His popularity extends from coast to coast.
My land extends over the hills on the horizon.
My memory extends back to my fourth year of life.
Our land extends beyond the fence to those trees.
The awning extends several feet over the sidewalk
The town's beachfront extends for more than a mile.
The River Nile extends as far south as Lake Victoria.
Their influence extends well beyond their immediate circle of friends.
Their knowledge of the family's history extends back to colonial times.
The main interest will be to see how he extends himself on the race-course.
I incline to the opinion that this principle extends to cases of religious discrimination.
The quaternary period of geologic time extends from the end of the tertiary period to the present.
Mrs. Griswold has been a teacher for so long that the sweep of her influence extends across three generations of the townspeople.
